Only place I know in Bury is Gigg Lane, so I did Gigg Lane to the NEC and it's 109 miles. 

Planning a 20 minute stop to top up your battery isn't concerning to me, I don't know why it would be to anyone. Sure, it's not a fantastic thing and by no means a benefit of EV ownership, but it's not concerning.

